; ============================================================
; Root
; ============================================================
;
; CANONICAL FLOOR PLAN — first-person retail interior, 16 m × 20 m floor
; with 3.5 m walls. Layout zones run back-to-front:
;
;          BACK WALL (Z = -10.05)
;   ----------------------------------------
;   |  CartRackLeft       CartRackRight     |  (back wall: cart racks)
;   |   X=-3.5, Z=-8.5     X=+3.5, Z=-8.5   |
;   |                                        |
;   |  TestingZone         GlassCase         |  (middle: testing + display island)
;   |  X=-4.8, Z=-7.14     X=0, Z=-4.0       |
;   |                          ConsoleShelf  |  (right side: console wall)
;   |                          X=+7.2, Z=-4.29
;   |                                        |
;   |  AccessoriesBin               Checkout |  (front zone: storage left, register right)
;   |  X=-7.52, Z=+1.43     X=+5.5, Z=+8.0  |
;   |  RefurbBench                           |
;   |  X=-7.28, Z=-7.14                      |
;   |                                        |
;   |             EntranceInterior           |
;   |               (X=0, Z=+9.35)           |
;   ----------------------------------------
;          MALL HALLWAY SIDE (Z = +10.05, ~3 m entrance gap)
;
; refurb_bench is rotated 90° flush against the left wall as a back-room
; work surface. The center walking aisle (X∈[-1.5,+1.5]) is unobstructed
; except for the GlassCase island at X=0, the intentional retail focal
; point. TestingZone is the co-located crt_demo_area (CRT prop + bench +
; neon panels + "Coming Soon" Label3D) and testing_station (Interactable
; wrapper, disabled until the testing flow is wired — see retro_games.gd).

[node name="RetroGames" type="Node3D"]
script = ExtResource("1")

