; ============================================================
; Zone Labels — Day-1 readability markers for the four primary zones
; (Shelves, Checkout, Exit / Mall, Backroom / Storage). Each label is a
; fixed-facing diegetic sign (no billboard) mounted on a backing panel
; oriented toward the player's primary approach direction:
;   • ShelvesLabel  → faces +Z (player approaching the back wall shelves)
;   • CheckoutLabel → faces -Z (customer queuing at the register)
;   • ExitLabel     → faces -Z (player walking toward the storefront)
;   • BackroomLabel → faces -X (player approaching the backroom door)
; Labels sit at Y≥2.7 so they clear all interactable slot zones
; (slots top at Y≤1.6). All four labels and their backings are in the
; "zone_label" group so future polish passes can bulk-hide them once
; real props communicate the layout
; (get_tree().call_group(&"zone_label", "set_visible", false)).
; ============================================================

